On September 15, 2017, the President signed two laws. The first law is H.R. 624, also known as the "Social Security Number Fraud Prevention Act of 2017." This law limits the use of Social Security numbers on federal documents that are sent through the mail. The second law is H.R. 1616, called the "Bob Dole Congressional Gold Medal Act." This law awards a Congressional gold medal to Bob Dole, in recognition of his service to the nation as a soldier, legislator, and statesman.